<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-074-110 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 278 233</DOCID><JOURNAL>Software Magazine  Sept 1991 v11 n11 p32(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Sentry Publishing Company Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>CGI Systems Inc. (Companies on the Move) (Field Report)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   CGI Systems Inc. (Planning).andO;Topic:     Company ProfileSoftware PublishersMainframe ComputersComputer-Aided Software EngineeringProgram Development SoftwareFinancial AnalysisMarketing StrategyStrategic Planning.andO;Feature:   illustrationportrait.andO;Caption:   Richard Ramsdell. (portrait)andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Following the unveiling of the IBM Repository Manager/MVS product nearly twoyears ago, CGI Systems Inc., Pearl River, N.Y., after much discussion,elected to continue offering a repository-based Case system.andM;&quot;There was a lot of discussion [within CGI] after IBM introduced therepository,&quot; commented Richard Ramsdell, president of CGI, the U.S.andP;  divisionof Paris-based CGI-Informatique.andP;  &quot;But we believed there was still a futurefor a robust repository.&quot;andM;To be safe, the company also decided to offer access to other top offerings,including those of IBM and Digital Equipment Corp., Ramsdell noted.andM;The decision was apparently correct.andP;  While the IBM offering continues tocome out in stages, CGI has quietly boosted its worldwide Case product andsupport revenues to $85 million.andP;  The U.S.andP;  operation, founded in 1982,accounts for $47 million in Case-related sales.andP;  Overall revenues for theparent firm total about $300 million.andM;The U.S.andP;  operation employs 500 workers, one-seventh of the company's overallworkforce of 3,500.andM;Its product line has expanded via acquisition (Yourdon Inc., and severalproducts from Transform Logic Inc.) and internal development (Paclan and arepository-driven automatic windowing facility) since the unveiling ofAD/Cycle.andM;Next year, Ramsdell said that CGI will add features to provide for thegeneration of &quot;true GUI applications&quot; and, a year later for distributedapplications for multivendor environments.andO;</TEXT></DOC>